  "prompt": "How do I play gem TD in DOTA2 when there is no internet?",
  "response": "To play Gem TD in DOTA 2 without an internet connection, you need to set up DOTA 2 to run offline and ensure the necessary game files and the Gem TD custom map are already downloaded on your computer. Here are the steps to do that:\n\n1. **Download DOTA 2 and Gem TD:**\n   - Make sure DOTA 2 is installed on your computer.\n   - Launch DOTA 2 while you still have an internet connection.\n   - Browse for Gem TD in the Arcade section and subscribe/download it so that it is saved to your computer.\n\n2. **Steam Offline Mode:**\n   - Open Steam.\n   - In the top-left corner, click on \"Steam\" and then select \"Go Offline.\"\n   - Confirm that you want to restart Steam in offline mode.\n\n3. **Launch DOTA 2:**\n   - While Steam is in offline mode, open DOTA 2.\n   - You should be able to access the game even without an internet connection, provided it does not require online validation.\n\n4. **Creating a Custom Lobby:**\n   - Go to the \"Play\" tab.\n   - Select \"Custom Lobby.\"\n   - Create a new lobby and ensure that it is set to \"Local.\"\n   - Choose Gem TD from the list of available custom maps (it should be there because you downloaded it earlier).\n\n5. **Start the Game:**\n   - Configure the lobby settings as desired (e.g., number of players, difficulty).\n   - Start the game and enjoy playing Gem TD offline.\n\nThese steps should allow you to play Gem TD even without an internet connection, assuming that all necessary data and files are already stored locally on your computer.",
